			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Leon Perelsztejn, who after his arrest in Ostrowiec Świętokrzyski was sent to the Treblinka extermination camp, where
					he was assigned to work at the tool house. He describes the crematoria and methods of burning corpses as well as his role in
					organizing the camp revolt.</p>
			</abstract>
