	<text>
		<body>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_perelsztejn_leon">Leon Perelsztejn</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/106)</p>
			<p>Typescript, 6 pages, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>
			<p>From the collection of the Warsaw Historical Commission for Investigation of Nazi Crimes</p>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010106_01.jpg"/> Testimony of <persName ref="#ehri_et_perelsztejn_leon">Leon Perelsztejn</persName></p>
			<p>Born <date when="1902-01-13">January 13, 1902</date>, in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html"
				>Warsaw</placeName></p>
			<p>Residing at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/771452/grochow.html">Grochów</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/771452/grochow.html">ul. Stanisława Augusta 24</placeName></p>
			<p>Regarding the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term>’ <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-254" type="subject">rebellion</term>, and preparations leading up to it,
				at the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka extermination
				camp</placeName></p>
			<p>On <date when="1942-09-27">September 27, 1942</date>, I was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598"
					type="subject">arrested</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec
					Kielecki</placeName>; <note type="gloss">Ostrowiec Świętokrzyski.</note> I had fled there from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName> in order to avoid being put in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> and taken to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName>. I was at <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName> from late <date when="1942-09"
					>September 1942</date> until <date when="1943-08-02">August 2, 1943</date>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> at <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName> was a typical <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-498" type="subject">extermination camp</term>. Jews from all over
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> and from abroad were brought there.
				During the month of <date when="1942-10">October</date>, until <date when="1942-11">November</date>, I was assigned to the group of
				Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">workers</term> that was sorting <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothing</term> [of the Jews who had been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>]. Later I was appointed as the
				warehouseman for the toolshop, where I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">worked</term>
				till my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. People were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">exterminated</term> in the following way: every day, a
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> of about twelve to twenty
				thousand people arrived. Three <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">trains</term> a day
				arrived at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> by the branch line. On
				average, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">train</term> had 60 cars with one
				hundred people each. After arriving, the people would be taken to the courtyard, which was surrounded by <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term>. They were told to strip naked, and
				their belongings were piled in a heap. There were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
					>women</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> and old people
				among those who arrived. Within two hours, the entire <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521"
					type="subject">transport</term> would be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
					>murdered</term>. This happened in the following way: in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486"
					type="subject">barracks</term> there were <q>shower</q> stalls, 10 stalls; people would be sent to the baths, one hundred people
				to a stall. In the stalls, there were towels and washbasins, which made it seem like real baths. After they were let in, with the push
				of a button, the doors would be hermetically sealed and the people <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010106_02.jpg"/> would be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-533" type="subject">suffocated</term> with some kind of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-534" type="subject">gas</term>, what kind, I do not know, within ten
				minutes. Ten minutes later, the floor moved aside automatically and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> fell into a hole several meters deep. A
				ditch several meters wide went from the pit for many hundreds of meters. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">corpses</term> were pulled on stretcher-carts by
				workers and carried out to piles, after which they were doused with gasoline and burned. Before people entered the stalls, their gold
				teeth were ripped out and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>’s hair was
				cut, the hair and gold were sent outside the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
					>camp</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term> who were
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">ill</term> were separated from each <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> and taken to a fence covered with a
				hedge with a sign that said <q>Lazaret</q> where they would be taken one by one [and] an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> man holding a revolver or a machine gun
				would <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">kill</term> them. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Prisoners</term> with <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004567">Red Cross</orgName> armbands would put the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-516" type="subject">corpses</term> in piles and burn them immediately.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">Untersturmführer</term>
				<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000382">Franz</persName>
				<note type="gloss">SS‑Hauptsturmführer Franz Paul Stangl, the camp commandant at the Treblinka extermination camp from August
					1942.</note> was in charge, he was the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
					>camp</term> commandant. His deputy was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject"
					>Hauptscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner</persName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner’s</persName> deputy was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">Scharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_miete_august">Mitte</persName>. They were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159"
					type="subject">Germans</term> from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"
					>SS</term> (Sonderkommando). There were forty-odd <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159"
					type="subject">Germans</term>. In addition to them, there were approximately 200 <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukrainians</placeName> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> service who, as <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">camp</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">guards</term>, also wore green uniforms and badges
				with the death’s-head and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. As a
				warehouseman, I could walk all over the entire <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
					>camp</term>, since my job was to check the tools of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557"
					type="subject">workers</term> who were doing various tasks in groups.</p>
			<p>A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term> named eng[ineer] <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_galewski">Galewski</persName> (from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>)
				was in charge of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term>-<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">workers</term>, he was [also] a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term>, a very decent person, who knew about
				our conspiracy and who, although he was not taking an active part in it, used to help all of us carry out our plans. <pb n="3"
					facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010106_03.jpg"/> In the warehouse where I was working, the idea for an armed revolt came up. About 150 meters
				from the warehouse was a weapons storeroom. We decided to get inside. A <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term> who was a locksmith had already made a
				key to the storeroom in March before my arrival, he carried it with him and did not let on in any way [that he was involved].
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_grundland">Grundland</persName> the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485"
					type="subject">capo</term> from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-280" type="subject">hospital</term> and I, along with a tailor from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/769250/kielce.html">Kielce</placeName>, who was about 46 years old, <q><persName
						ref="#ehri_et_moniek">Moniek</persName></q>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485"
					type="subject">capo</term> from the first <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject"
					>barracks</term>, who was about 18 or 19, one [fellow] known as <q><persName ref="#ehri_et_jacek">Jacek</persName></q>, and
				several other people, whose names I don’t remember, neither first nor last names, worked out a plan to take over the weapons
				storeroom, which we did on <date when="1943-08-02">August 2, 1943</date>.</p>
			<p>Our first earlier attempt was unsuccessful and twelve people - who had been betrayed by a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term>, a man who used to make wire mesh for
				a living from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3100946/czestochowa.html">Częstochowa</placeName> - paid for it with their
				lives. We were supposed to take over the warehouse and begin the action around <date when="1943-07-12">July 12, 1943</date>. Having
				been unable to get into the weapons storeroom that day, we postponed the action. A few days later, fourteen people from various <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">work</term> columns who had been taking part in the
				conspiracy were taken away. I was released along with a certain turner, whose name I do not remember, because there were no other
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term> to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">work</term> in our positions, and despite being
				beaten, we did not confess and they did not have any evidence against us. Those twelve were taken away to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName> II, <note type="gloss">The
					extermination camp is described in the literature as Treblinka II, and the labor camp next to it as Treblinka I. The witness calls
					Treblinka I part of the camp in which prisoners were kept, Treblinka II as the actual extermination center and Treblinka III as
					the labor camp</note> where they were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
					>shot</term>. We did not see them <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">die</term>,
				but we heard the shots from a distance of 300 meters.</p>
			<p>We did not stop working on new plans for a revolt, however. At night, we worked in strict secrecy. In each group of workers, we chose
				people, former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term>, who knew how to use
				weapons, and we assigned them specific military tasks in the action and did not make them privy to our plans, and told them to wait
				for our signal. We assigned three to set the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject"
					>barracks</term> on fire <pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010106_04.jpg"/> with gasoline. I had the task of storming the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> headquarters, destroying the telephone and
				disposing of the secretary, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_messing">Messing</persName>, and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477"
					type="subject">Stabsscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_stadie_otto">Stadi</persName>, <note type="gloss">Stabsscharführer was not a rank but a position of company
					sergeant major.</note> which I was to do with eight other people. The locksmith gave us the key. Two <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">boys</term>, 18 or 19 years old, who <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">worked</term> cleaning the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term>, observed the weapons storeroom for
				two weeks and had the task of getting inside and passing the weapons through the barred window. The masons were supposed to come with
				carts used for carting away rubble and take the weapons to the garage, where there was an enormous cellar. From there, when the signal
				was given, the weapons were to be distributed and the action was to start. The second and final attempt was to be made on <date
					when="1943-08-02">August 2</date>, at 4:15 p.m., which was when the fighting was supposed to begin. One of the cleaners,
						<q><persName ref="#ehri_et_jacek">Jacek</persName></q>, entered the weapons storeroom at 1:15 p.m., the second stood at the
				door on guard. <persName ref="#ehri_et_jacek">Jacek</persName> passed all the weapons through the window to the men with the carts.
				They took them to the garage. At 2:30 p.m., weapons began to be distributed from the garage to all the groups of workers throughout
				the entire <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. All the designated former
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term> got weapons. At 4:15 p.m., when
				the action was supposed to start, I was waiting at the storeroom with a revolver that had been ready for a month. The detailed plan
				had been set for that time because a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">train</term> of
				Jewish and <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Polish</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term> going from <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-557" type="subject">work</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765328/malkinia-gorna.html">Małkinia</placeName> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1913" type="camp">Treblinka III</placeName>
				<note type="gloss">Treblinka III – labor camp (actually Treblinka I).</note> would pass through the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> as it did every day at that time, and we
				wanted to intercept them and have them join our action. They were not privy to the plan. At 3:35 p.m., two workers who came to the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term> for their things roused the
				suspicion of the confidant <q><persName ref="#ehri_et_kuba">Kuba</persName></q>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">barracks elder</term>, who summoned <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">Hauptscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner</persName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner</persName> summoned them to
				the square in front of my door, searched them, found money on them, began to whip them and wanted to shoot them. <pb n="5"
					facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010106_05.jpg"/> When I saw that, I gave the signal to start the action through the back window. The tailor
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_zalcberg">Zalcberg</persName>, from the second <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term>, began <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-254" type="subject">shooting</term> at <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner</persName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner</persName> started running towards
				his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term> to get a machine gun. The action
				began. No longer able to carry out my task, my people and I cut through the barbed wire in order to get to the back entrance to the
				tower, where the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukrainians</placeName> were. A former lieutenant in the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1077" type="subject">army</term>, whose first name was <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_rudolf">Rudolf</persName>, had the most important task. He and a second <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovakia</placeName> took a heavy machine gun by cart with some
				people to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> zoo, went into the little
				tower and began shooting at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>’s
				headquarters and the guard posts. None of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject"
					>Germans</term> or <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukrainians</placeName> who were there could get
				out, and they all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term> were set on fire. During the
				fighting, many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term>, but almost the entire <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">camp staff</term> at that time <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> on the spot. The whole <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was on fire. I saw <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_kuttner_kurt">Kittner</persName> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
					type="subject">SS-man</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_suchomel_franz">Suchomil</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">die</term> with my own eyes, shot in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-486" type="subject">barracks</term> window. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term>, head of the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> Strasebahn, whose last name I do not remember, was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> by a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term> who worked as a driver. His killer was
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> by some <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/690791/ukraine.html">Ukrainian</placeName>. The action was lightning-quick. At 4:30 p.m. the entire
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>, with or without weapons, was free.
				And we fled to the surrounding forests. No one chased us. Unfortunately we did not manage to include the train with the workers,
				because when shots were heard, it was stopped before it reached us. Everyone who was [physically] able <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> from <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName> I and II. Engineer <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_galewski">Galewski</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> with me. Unfortunately after a few
				kilometers, his nerves failed him, he took some poison from his pocket, swallowed it and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> immediately, right in front of my eyes. I
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>
				<pb n="6" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010106_06.jpg"/> into the forest with a group of several other <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term>, and after two weeks of wandering, I
				made it to my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">family</term>, where I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term>. I was in the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/763121/opatow.html">Opatów</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/769250/kielce.html">Kielce</placeName> regions the whole time, until those areas were <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573">liberated</term> by the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Red Army</orgName>. On <date when="1945-01-21">January 21,
					1945</date>, I was in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Praga</placeName>, where I am now living. All
				the facts I have described are true. I read this document before signing it.</p>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, <date when="1945-03-09">March 9, 1945</date></p>
			<p>(-) <persName ref="#ehri_et_perelsztejn_leon">Leon Perelsztejn</persName></p>
			<p>Recorded by <persName ref="#ehri_et_swiderski_b.">B. Świderski</persName>, M.A.</p>
